Sentencas: Low temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs) are favourable for various applications such as vehicles, residual power generations, and even portable chargers.
Titulo: Nano-Composite Ni-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 Anode Functional Layer for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: However, low power density is considered as a main obstacle for LT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Nano-Composite Ni-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 Anode Functional Layer for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Many studies concentrate on improving the cathode part for better oxygen dissociation and reducing the electrolyte thickness for faster oxygen transfer.
Titulo: Nano-Composite Ni-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 Anode Functional Layer for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: However, the anode part and the interface between anode and electrolyte can significantly contribute to increasing power density at low temperatures.
Titulo: Nano-Composite Ni-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 Anode Functional Layer for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In this study, the nano-composite Ni-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 anode functional layer (AFL) powder with core/shell-like shape is prepared for LT-SOFCs with high power density.
Titulo: Nano-Composite Ni-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 Anode Functional Layer for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The AFL deposited on the anode supports by dip-coating process had better Ni and Ce distribution and the interface between the electrolyte and the AFL are well connected.
Titulo: Nano-Composite Ni-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 Anode Functional Layer for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In hydrogen condition, the maximum power density of 0.98 Wcm(-2) appears at 600 degrees C in the cell with the AFL Even at 450 degrees C, the cell has 0.34 Wcm(-2) in the maximum power density, which is appropriate for LT-SOFCs operation.
Titulo: Nano-Composite Ni-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 Anode Functional Layer for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Based on the performance at low temperature, additional cell tests are conducted on the cell with the AFL in various fuel conditions including methane and ammonia.
Titulo: Nano-Composite Ni-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 Anode Functional Layer for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
